OL,6,FThe court heard that Hardcastle
OL,7,Finflicted a severe head injury to
OL,8,FDamion by either forcefully shaking
OL,9,Fhim and then banging his head against
OL,10,Fa solid object or directly caused
OL,11,FDamion's head to collide with a solid
OL,12,Fobject with such force, that his it
OL,13,Fcaused significant injuries to his
OL,14,Fneck and eyes.
OL,16,FDamion was taken to hospital following
OL,17,Fthe assault, but his injuries were
OL,18,Funsurvivable and he died two days
OL,19,Flater.
